    "content_hash": "a5810aa39cf483cc",
    "department": "Growth",
    "description": "About Juicebox\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe’re hiring a Content Marketing Manager to become the voice of Juicebox.\n\nThis role owns the content that prospects and customers experience outside the product, including blog posts, case studies, videos, SEO content, and more.\n\nYou’ll work closely with the marketing team and our customers to tell the stories of how companies are using Juicebox to transform their hiring.\n\nYou Will\n\n - Own Juicebox’s content strategy and execution\n\n - Write and publish blog https://juicebox.ai/blog/articles posts, case studies, and SEO content\n\n - Interview customers and create compelling customer stories https://juicebox.ai/customers\n\n - Produce additional content formats including videos, guides, and thought leadership\n\n - Manage and edit work from external writers and contributors, including social media content\n\n - Identify opportunities for new content initiatives and distribution channels\n\n - Ensure all published content reflects Juicebox’s voice, brand, and product expertise\n\n - Help make SEO a major customer acquisition channel\n   \n\nYou Have\n\n - 2+ years of B2B content marketing experience (4+ preferred)\n\n - Strong writing and storytelling ability\n\n - Experience producing SEO-driven content\n\n - Familiarity with tools like Semrush, Profound, or similar SEO / AEO platforms\n\n - Ability to work with external writers and maintain a consistent voice\n\n - Strong ownership mentality and ability to operate independently",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
